WHO   — The Man-Child & the Father — the quest to be seen
WHAT  — The oldest parable in a moped helmet: every ridiculous plot beat is in service of a son needing his father to say he's proud.
WHERE — HRD · Hot Rod (2007)  Framework inputs: Hot Rod (2007, dir. Akiva Schaffer, The Lonely Island/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the comedy is a disguise for this single ancient hunger, and naming it is the parabolic read.
HOW   — By making the entire heroic quest a roundabout way to hear four words: 'I'm proud of you.'

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the oldest story there is, wearing a helmet: a son who will do anything, however dumb, to be seen by his father.

